@bp 2.11 parallelism and instructions: synchronization
@bq parallel execution
@4o data race: two memory accesses form a data race if they
are from different threads to the same location, at least one
is a write, and occur one after the other
@4p easier when independent, often need to cooperate
@4q set of primitives to read/modify atomically (nothing
else interposes itself between read/write)
@4r atomic exchange/swap: interchanges a value in register
for value in memory
@4s simple lock: 0 means lock is free, 1, available
@4t set lock: exchange of 1
@4u value returned 1 (unavail) or 0 (free)
@4v when 0 returned, value set to 1, preventing any
competing exchange
@4w atomicity: memory write/read in a single, uninterruptible instruction
@4x instruction pair, 2nd instruction determines if pair was executed
as if atomic
@4y effectively atomic: appears as if all other procedure operations
appeared before/after pair
@4z load linked
@50 store conditional
@51 store value of a (presumably different) register
@52 change register value to 1 if successful, 0 if failure
